Here is the code that performs what you asked for. It defines a function called `clean_column` which takes a string as input (the column name) and returns another string with the desired transformations applied to it.

```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    # Lowercase the column name
    col = lowercase(col);
    # Remove leading and trailing whitespace
    col = strip(col);
    # Replace spaces and hyphens with underscores
    return replace(col, " " => "_", "-" => "_");
end
```

If you need to perform more complex transformations on your column names, please specify what they are. I can help you modify this function to meet your needs.
